ONE person was killed and three others injured after a delivery truck crashed into a stationary light motor vehicle on Wednesday, 20 July, on the R21 in Olifantsfontein. Emer-G-Med spokesman Kyle van Reenen said their paramedics responded to the scene at 4am. And four men, in their 30s and seated in the car at the time of impact, suffered injuries. ALSO READ: How to find cheaper petrol in Mzansi! “Two men were entrapped in the wreckage. One suffered fatal injuries and was declared dead at the scene, while the second was in a critical condition,” said Van Reenen in a statement. He said that other patients were taken to a nearby hospital for further care. “Two other passengers suffered moderate injuries and were treated and stabilised on the scene before being taken to a nearby hospital,” Van Reenen said.